AB  - Edible mushroom polysaccharides, as one of the main biological activities of mushrooms, have anti-tumour, Edible mushroom polysacchardes, as one of the main biological activties of mushrooms, have anti-tumour, anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, immune regulation and other functions. Especially because of its anti-tumour ti-nflammatry, antioxidant, immune regulation and other functions. Especilly because of its anti-tumour andimmunomodulatory activity, it has been used in the clinical treatment of various diseases. Recent studies have focused on mushroom polysaccharides' functional properties, which may be related to their chemical and immunomodulatory activity, it has been used in the linical treament of varous diseases. Recent studies have focu ed on mushroom polysacchardes functiona propertes, which may be related to their chemical structures. This review aims to clarify the biological activity of edible mushroom polysaccharides and their medicinal potential in human health and to reveal the relationship between chemical structure and the structures. This review aims to c arify the biological actvity of edible mushroom polysaccharides and their medcinal potential in human health and to revea biological activity of edible mushroom polysaccharides.
